# Rule: .agents/README.md

This is the entry point to the agent self-describing layer. It must:

- show the layout of `.agents/` (folders + files);
- one-line each role (`RULES.md`, `rules/`, `skills/`, `memory/`);
- point at the two skills that govern writes
  (`.agents/skills/navigating-project-docs/SKILL.md` and
  `.agents/skills/maintaining-agents-dir/SKILL.md`);
- list what does **not** live here (product code, product docs,
  build tooling, CI workflows).

## Template

```markdown
# `.agents/` — <one-line role>

> **What this folder is.** <one paragraph>

## Layout

<tree>

## Roles (one line each)

| File | Role | Read first? |
|------|------|------------|
| … | … | … |

## How to add things

- **…** → load `.agents/skills/.../SKILL.md`.
- **…** → load `.agents/skills/.../SKILL.md`.

## What does NOT live here
```